<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Vignaud</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-25"><hi rend="italic">February 25,
                                    1895</hi></date>. (Received Feb. 25.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>A decree of the minister of agriculture, gazetted this morning, forbids
                            the importation into France, until further orders, of cattle coming from
                            the United States. Cattle shipped before February 24 will be admitted
                            under certain restrictions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Vignaud</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>